tment with my academic advisor/counselor? You will schedule that appointment through our front desk by calling 940-565-4115 or schedule in person Chilton Hall (CHIL), Room 289. How do I change my major (for students already attending UNT)? You meet with the appropriate academic advisor/counselor for the intended major and change during that meeting. Note: Individuals changing to anthropology must first meet with a faculty member in the anthropology department. Their number is 940-565-2290. They are located in Chilton 330Q. I am not doing well in my course, where can I go for help? The Learning Center: http://www.unt.edu/lc/ Math Tutor Lab: http://www.math.unt.edu/mathlab/ Economics Help Center: http://economics.unt.edu/news/help-center-news History Help Center: https://history.unt.edu/department-information/history-help-center University Writing Lab: http://ltc.unt.edu/node/362 What other helpful resources exist at UNT? Money Management Center: http://moneymanagement.unt.edu/ Counseling & Testing: http://www.unt.edu/cat/ Career Center: http://careercenter.unt.edu/ Other resources can be found on this site under Student Activities and Services: http://www.unt.edu/campus-life.htm Where do I go to find out what is happening on campus and to get more involved? Events Calendars: http://calendar.unt.edu/calendar.cfm Student Activities Center: http://studentactivities.unt.edu/  I am interested in doing an internship for academic credit, how do I start that process? Contact the Internships office within the Division of Student Affairs: http://studentaffairs.unt.edu/internships Also speak with your academic advisor/counselor about any special procedures for your major What is the best e-mail to use when contacting my academic advisor/counselor and instructors? EagleConnect It can be found through my.unt.edu or eagleconnect.unt.edu.  It is recommended that all e-mail be initiated from this account even if you have it forwarding to another account (i.e. Gmail, Yahoo, etc.) Visit Us Chilton Hall 410 S. Avenue C Denton, TX 76201 Mail Us University of North Texas 1155 Union Circle #311340 Denton, TX 76203 Contact Us 940-565-2239 HPS@unt.edu Site last updated on May 08, 2017 Disclaimer| AA/EOE/ADA| Privacy| Electronic Accessibility| State of Texas Online| Emergency Preparedness| THECB Online Resume System Student Consumer Information| UNT Compliance Hotline| Governors Committee on People with Disabilities| Texas Veterans Portal| UNT Home Site last updated on May 08, 2017 | Important Links 